description.plain: “The Melbourne 5 piece has worked tirelessly to create something inherently familiar, yet at the same time unashamedly different. Taking the heavy riffs of their downbeat and deathcore contemporaries, mixing that with the groove of the current wave of nu-metal bands, and adding a melody that completely their own; Alpha Wolf are carving out their own place in the Australian heavy scene.” – Greyscale Records

description.plain:
“Golden Fate” is a subtle reference to the Golden Gate suicide jumpers. “Gut Ache” is referring to the feeling experienced by friends and family after a suicide victim takes their own life.
This song displays the feeling of regret and guilt one may experience after losing a loved one to suicide. The lack of consideration towards warning signs causes the blaming of oneself, and can lead one to believe they are partially responsible for the death of their loved one, but it is ultimately too late.
